{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.39",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 39,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 39 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:1",
      "text": "I said, “I will guard my ways, that I may not sin with my tongue; I will bridle my mouth, so long as the wicked are in my presence.”",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:2",
      "text": "I was dumb and silent, I held my peace to no avail; my distress grew worse,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:3",
      "text": "my heart became hot within me. As I mused, the fire burned; then I spoke with my tongue:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:4",
      "text": "“ Lord, let me know my end, and what is the measure of my days; let me know how fleeting my life is!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:5",
      "text": "Behold, thou hast made my days a few handbreadths, and my lifetime is as nothing in thy sight. Surely every man stands as a mere breath!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:6",
      "text": "Surely man goes about as a shadow! Surely for naught are they in turmoil; man heaps up, and knows not who will gather!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:7",
      "text": "“And now, Lord, for what do I wait? My hope is in thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:8",
      "text": "Deliver me from all my transgressions. Make me not the scorn of the fool!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:9",
      "text": "I am dumb, I do not open my mouth; for it is thou who hast done it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:10",
      "text": "Remove thy stroke from me; I am spent by the blows of thy hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:11",
      "text": "When thou dost chasten man with rebukes for sin, thou dost consume like a moth what is dear to him; surely every man is a mere breath!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:12",
      "text": "“Hear my prayer, O Lord, and give ear to my cry; hold not thy peace at my tears! For I am thy passing guest, a sojourner, like all my fathers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.39.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 39:13",
      "text": "Look away from me, that I may know gladness, before I depart and be no more!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
